00:21:35,364 --> 00:21:36,892
Damn it!

237
00:21:37,044 --> 00:21:38,334
I'm totally screwed.

238
00:21:41,684 --> 00:21:43,213
Oh!

239
00:21:49,844 --> 00:21:52,005
- Ram him.
- What are you doing?

240
00:21:57,444 --> 00:21:59,407
<i>- Oh, my God.
- Keep going.</i>

241
00:22:00,004 --> 00:22:02,765
You're an idiot.
That's assault with a deadly weapon.

242
00:22:02,924 --> 00:22:04,692
They could shoot at us now.

243
00:22:06,605 --> 00:22:09,004
<i>- Speed up.
- Shit.</i>

244
00:22:10,404 --> 00:22:11,844
<i>Turn right now.</i>

245
00:22:16,805 --> 00:22:19,204
<i>Remember, if they catch you...</i>

246
00:22:20,164 --> 00:22:21,484
<i>you'll be a widower.</i>

247
00:22:26,884 --> 00:22:28,564
<i>- Turn left.
- Oh, shit.</i>

248
00:22:32,564 --> 00:22:34,648
<i>- Force him off the road.
- Look out!</i>

249
00:22:36,403 --> 00:22:38,892
- This is not very subtle you know!
- What are you talking about?

250
00:22:39,045 --> 00:22:41,292
You're not making yourself
very hard to find.

251
00:22:47,524 --> 00:22:50,447
God, I promise I'll be good from now on.
Please let me live.

252
00:22:50,603 --> 00:22:52,807
<i>- You're really not helping, okay?
- Turn right.</i>

253
00:23:00,963 --> 00:23:02,492
Great.

254
00:23:12,723 --> 00:23:14,252
<i>Turn right down the alley.</i>

255
00:23:16,164 --> 00:23:17,243
Stop!

256
00:23:21,083 --> 00:23:22,250
Holy shit.

257
00:23:26,403 --> 00:23:28,411
- 2 minutes.
- We're gonna die, please stop!

258
00:23:38,725 --> 00:23:40,643
<i>I don't think you'll make it.</i>

259
00:23:44,963 --> 00:23:48,248
- What are you doing?
- Take a deep breath, okay? And calm down.

260
00:23:53,644 --> 00:23:55,051
Shit.

261
00:23:58,763 --> 00:24:00,323
<i>I wouldn't relax just yet.</i>

262
00:24:03,843 --> 00:24:05,971
- Shit.
- Not again.

263
00:24:06,123 --> 00:24:08,251
<i>- Did you think we were done?
- No, don't!</i>

264
00:24:09,603 --> 00:24:10,682
God!

265
00:24:17,763 --> 00:24:19,204
<i>You're running out of time.</i>

266
00:24:21,122 --> 00:24:22,966
Oh! Oh!

267
00:24:23,243 --> 00:24:24,410
<i>Tick tock, tick tock.</i>

268
00:24:31,603 --> 00:24:33,130
<i>You have less than a minute.</i>

269
00:24:33,283 --> 00:24:35,530
<i>- Turn into the park.
- No, not the park!</i>

270
00:24:35,682 --> 00:24:37,330
Here we go.

271
00:24:40,322 --> 00:24:42,406
<i>Your wife's time is running out.</i>

272
00:24:43,963 --> 00:24:45,850
- Watch out!
- Unh!

273
00:24:46,002 --> 00:24:48,523
<i>- Go through the intersection.
- All right, hold on!</i>

274
00:24:57,523 --> 00:24:59,563
<i>Not much time, Mr. Magna.</i>

275
00:25:00,202 --> 00:25:01,522
Oh, no!

276
00:25:04,321 --> 00:25:07,083
- No, please don't! Don't!
- Yep, yep, yep, hold on!

277
00:25:07,243 --> 00:25:08,650
<i>5...</i>

278
00:25:08,802 --> 00:25:10,603
- ...4...
- Come on, come on, come on!

279
00:25:10,762 --> 00:25:12,170
<i>...3...</i>

280
00:25:12,322 --> 00:25:13,969
<i>- ...2...
- Oh!</i>

281
00:25:14,122 --> 00:25:15,443
<i>...1...</i>

282
00:25:15,602 --> 00:25:19,050
...zero. Bravo, Mr. Magna.
Well done.

283
00:25:20,001 --> 00:25:22,250
Bravo. Your wife lives...

284
00:25:23,241 --> 00:25:24,409
<i>...for now.</i>

285
00:25:28,642 --> 00:25:30,247
Well done.

286
00:25:47,042 --> 00:25:48,089
Answer.

287
00:25:48,241 --> 00:25:52,082
Brent Magna is
both reckless and fearful.

288
00:25:52,242 --> 00:25:53,726
He is, in short...

289
00:25:53,882 --> 00:25:58,083
...a dangerous driver
and should pursue another profession.

290
00:25:58,242 --> 00:26:01,449
Remember that review?
It wasn't very flattering.

291
00:26:01,602 --> 00:26:03,926
<i>They're blind to your real talents...</i>

292
00:26:04,082 --> 00:26:06,930
<i>...which are perfectly
suited to my needs.</i>

293
00:26:07,083 --> 00:26:08,249
Do I know you?

294
00:26:08,401 --> 00:26:10,290
<i>I know you, Mr. Magna...</i>

295
00:26:10,442 --> 00:26:12,166
<i>- ...and I believe in you.
- Listen.</i>

296
00:26:12,322 --> 00:26:15,323
I need to know when this is all
gonna be over, all right? I need--

297
00:26:17,522 --> 00:26:18,766
What are you doing?

298
00:26:18,921 --> 00:26:21,202
Hey, what are you doing?

299
00:26:23,121 --> 00:26:25,446
- I hate you.
- Yeah, I love you.

300
00:26:25,603 --> 00:26:29,170
You realize I'll just have to buy another
limited edition Shelby Super Snake...

301
00:26:29,322 --> 00:26:33,643
...take another 6 months to re-time the cams,
open up the intake and customize it.

302
00:26:33,801 --> 00:26:36,082
And then I'm gonna drive
it over your face.

303
00:26:36,242 --> 00:26:39,689
- You sure know a lot about cars for--
- A girl?

304
00:26:39,842 --> 00:26:41,205
Yeah.

305
00:26:41,761 --> 00:26:43,082
Wow.

306
00:26:44,002 --> 00:26:47,690
<i>I like fast cars and computers
and boy things, how butch.</i>

307
00:26:47,842 --> 00:26:49,687
It's the 21st century,
you should join it.

308
00:26:53,281 --> 00:26:55,529
- What are you doing?
- I'm documenting this shit.

309
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:57,842
I'm not going to jail
after we get arrested.

310
00:26:58,001 --> 00:27:00,969
- Well, nobody's gonna get caught, okay?
- That's right, I forgot.

311
00:27:01,121 --> 00:27:05,169
We're just gonna die because you're a dumb-ass
who attacks the police with a damn car.

312
00:27:05,320 --> 00:27:07,088
Now every cop in this entire country...

313
00:27:07,242 --> 00:27:10,089
...is hoping to run to us, to put a couple bullets
in our heads. That's a good plan.

314
00:27:10,241 --> 00:27:12,565
- We are alive.
- Barely.

315
00:27:12,802 --> 00:27:14,330
Not much of a thinker are you?

316
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:17,928
Well you know, I didn't actually graduate
from charm school like you so maybe...

317
00:27:18,081 --> 00:27:21,290
...you know someday you can give me
some tutoring or something.

318
00:27:22,521 --> 00:27:25,370
This is what he did
to my beautiful, beautiful paint job.

319
00:27:25,521 --> 00:27:26,809
Just get in the car.

320
00:27:26,961 --> 00:27:31,206
This is all the crap that he drilled
into my carbon fiber interior.

321
00:27:31,361 --> 00:27:33,204
And this is the dumb-ass
who got me into this mess.

322
00:27:33,362 --> 00:27:35,849
- Stop filming me, all right?
- Wave hi to the judge.

323
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:40,921
- Say hi to all your new friends in jail.
- Hey! Put that thing away! I'm trying-- Just stop it.

324
00:27:42,720 --> 00:27:46,289
What is--? You're like ADD or something.
What are you fiddling with now?

325
00:27:46,440 --> 00:27:48,089
- Stop doing that.
- Why?

326
00:27:48,241 --> 00:27:50,881
Because this guy is watching us, okay?

327
00:27:51,041 --> 00:27:53,441
- And I need you to stop--
- I know what I'm doing.

328
00:27:53,601 --> 00:27:56,961
- Just sit still and listen to me for 2 seconds.
- I know what I'm doing.

329
00:27:57,120 --> 00:27:59,129
See, I went to school
and I know things...

330
00:27:59,281 --> 00:28:02,446
...which is why I don't have to
steal stuff, like some people.

331
00:28:03,922 --> 00:28:07,446
If you're so smart, you tell me what's
going on with all these cameras, huh?

332
00:28:15,201 --> 00:28:16,969
They're all linked to a single feed.

333
00:28:17,121 --> 00:28:21,443
It's not only encrypted, but it's
piggybacking on a public server.

334
00:28:21,601 --> 00:28:22,680
Huh?

335
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:26,729
It means that they're hosting
this live feed from these cameras...

336
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:29,641
...on a government server
without them knowing about it.

337
00:28:30,401 --> 00:28:33,162
So anybody can watch it, even us.

338
00:28:39,080 --> 00:28:40,848
- Wait a second.
- What?

339
00:28:41,001 --> 00:28:44,043
- These aren't coming from the same place.
- Where are they coming from?

340
00:28:44,200 --> 00:28:46,164
Looks like a parking garage.

341
00:28:46,320 --> 00:28:48,961
- Can you tell where it is?
- I don't know. Could be anywhere.

342
00:28:49,120 --> 00:28:52,721
- Do you think it's where he might be?
- Doubt it. But he can see it.

343
00:28:52,881 --> 00:28:54,442
I don't like the fact that he's watching us.

344
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:56,640
Do you think you can track him
with that thing?

345
00:28:56,801 --> 00:28:59,768
No, and if anyone did,
he would just dump the IP address.

346
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:03,488
As long as his feed is hosted remotely,
there's no way to find it.

347
00:29:03,640 --> 00:29:05,843
- And that thing isn't really well-hidden.
- What?

348
00:29:05,999 --> 00:29:07,288
Microphone.

349
00:29:07,441 --> 00:29:09,764
- Oh, so he's listening to us too?
- Probably.

350
00:29:12,320 --> 00:29:14,720
Well, I'll give you this,
you are bright.

351
00:29:16,799 --> 00:29:18,404
It's called being educated.

352
00:29:18,561 --> 00:29:21,200
You should look into it
when you're not committing crimes.

353
00:29:21,360 --> 00:29:23,999
Scratch that, you'll be in jail.

354
00:29:35,680 --> 00:29:36,641
All right, answer.

355
00:29:36,799 --> 00:29:39,048
Pull up power plant on the GPS.

356
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:42,927
We're kind of busy right now.

357
00:29:44,079 --> 00:29:45,520
Learn to multitask.

358
00:29:47,761 --> 00:29:50,565
Or let your new little friend help you.
Look under the visor.

359
00:29:52,119 --> 00:29:53,440
<i>Won't you do that?</i>

360
00:29:54,880 --> 00:29:56,963
<i>I'm uploading a new set of directions.</i>

361
00:29:58,479 --> 00:30:00,084
That's the city power plant.

362
00:30:01,039 --> 00:30:02,764
At exactly 11:30...

363
00:30:02,919 --> 00:30:04,240
...you will be there.

364
00:30:07,399 --> 00:30:09,047
Why are we going to the power plant?

365
00:30:11,919 --> 00:30:13,599
Always so inquisitive.

366
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:15,363
I like it.

367
00:30:26,400 --> 00:30:28,844
Now listen carefully,
you're to break into the control room.

368
00:30:29,279 --> 00:30:31,288
Access the remote system...

369
00:30:31,439 --> 00:30:33,447
- ...and insert that drive.
- What will that do?

370
00:30:33,598 --> 00:30:36,283
You're a clever girl.
I'm sure you'll figure it out.

371
00:30:38,799 --> 00:30:42,159
He wants to cut the power off.
Why do you want to cut the power?

372
00:30:42,919 --> 00:30:44,686
You have some time until 11:30.

373
00:30:45,439 --> 00:30:48,047
I wouldn't spend it
trying to figure out my motives.

374
00:30:51,838 --> 00:30:53,202
He's a real asshole.

375
00:31:27,758 --> 00:31:29,121
So you don't know who that is?

376
00:31:31,599 --> 00:31:32,799
No.

377
00:31:33,718 --> 00:31:35,683
- No idea?
- I got ideas.

378
00:31:36,719 --> 00:31:39,043
People I used to work with...

379
00:31:39,198 --> 00:31:41,599
...but nobody I know could set up
something like this.

380
00:31:42,998 --> 00:31:45,606
- So why you?
- Because I can drive.

381
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:49,280
- That's debatable.
- No, I mean, I used to race.

382
00:31:49,878 --> 00:31:53,086
- Really?
- Really.

383
00:31:53,238 --> 00:31:55,846
Professionally, like, real racing.

384
00:31:55,999 --> 00:31:58,083
Don't think I ever saw you on TV.

385
00:31:58,238 --> 00:32:00,638
There was a couple weeks
there where you might have.

386
00:32:01,158 --> 00:32:02,643
And?

387
00:32:04,158 --> 00:32:05,926
And what?

388
00:32:09,278 --> 00:32:11,078
I washed out.

389
00:32:14,837 --> 00:32:16,201
How come?

390
00:32:16,918 --> 00:32:19,558
I don't know, I just did.
Doesn't matter now.

391
00:32:20,477 --> 00:32:22,399
That's a pretty shitty answer.

392
00:32:28,158 --> 00:32:31,922
I washed out because I believed
everybody who told me how great I was.

393
00:32:32,077 --> 00:32:36,157
Turns out the only thing I was great at
was wrecking expensive cars.

394
00:32:36,959 --> 00:32:39,239
So I fell off the pro circuit
and I owed a bunch of money.

395
00:32:39,397 --> 00:32:41,918
This is the only thing
I was ever any good at...

396
00:32:42,118 --> 00:32:45,118
...so I took whatever job
paid the most.

397
00:32:47,078 --> 00:32:49,642
I did some things I'm not proud of.

398
00:32:52,477 --> 00:32:55,839
But then I got out of it. And this...

399
00:32:56,917 --> 00:32:58,565
...is why.

400
00:33:04,717 --> 00:33:06,517
She's beautiful.

401
00:33:08,638 --> 00:33:11,441
- Is she from here?
- Yeah.

402
00:33:12,438 --> 00:33:15,525
She always wanted to come back,
so we thought...

403
00:33:15,678 --> 00:33:19,442
...it'd be a good place
to lay low and start over.

404
00:33:19,598 --> 00:33:22,325
Then I come home from work today,
the door is busted open...

405
00:33:22,477 --> 00:33:25,686
...the place is a wreck,
there's blood on the floor.

406
00:33:26,078 --> 00:33:31,282
My cell phone rings and this voice tells me
if I ever wanna s--

407
00:33:33,276 --> 00:33:35,242
If I ever wanna see her again...

408
00:33:35,997 --> 00:33:38,158
...I gotta do this job.

409
00:33:41,078 --> 00:33:43,477
And if I tell anyone, she'll be dead.

410
00:33:46,837 --> 00:33:50,121
Next thing you know,
I'm driving around in your car.

411
00:33:54,998 --> 00:33:56,797
You souped this thing up yourself?

412
00:33:58,037 --> 00:34:00,045
Yeah, it was a graduation present.

413
00:34:00,477 --> 00:34:03,445
Nice. Something tells me
your dad's not a mechanic.

414
00:34:06,716 --> 00:34:08,965
He's the CEO
of one of the largest banks in town.

415
00:34:09,118 --> 00:34:13,001
We moved here about 2 years ago
for him to take it over.

416
00:34:15,037 --> 00:34:18,966
I barely see him, but this car
is the nicest gift he ever gave me.

417
00:34:21,517 --> 00:34:23,197
Well, I'm sorry about all the damage.

418
00:34:26,076 --> 00:34:29,165
You know, you could also apologize
for taking me hostage.

419
00:34:29,756 --> 00:34:31,885
And you could apologize
for putting a gun in my face.

420
00:34:32,037 --> 00:34:33,520
I will if you let me out.

421
00:34:33,917 --> 00:34:36,961
There's only one thing
I'm concerned about right now...

422
00:34:37,117 --> 00:34:39,998
...and I'm gonna do whatever I have to
to get her back.

423
00:34:40,157 --> 00:34:43,517
So if he says you gotta stay in the car,
you gotta stay in the car.

424
00:34:43,676 --> 00:34:45,281
And where does that get you?

425
00:34:46,238 --> 00:34:48,244
Why is this happening?
What is he after?

426
00:34:49,836 --> 00:34:52,160
You clearly haven't
thought this through.

427
00:34:52,956 --> 00:34:56,840
What happens when this is done
and he gets what he wants?

428
00:34:56,996 --> 00:34:59,604
Why would he even give her back to you?

429
00:35:00,476 --> 00:35:03,924
If I were him, I'd kill her
and I'd probably kill you.

430
00:35:04,076 --> 00:35:06,957
- Shit.
- What?

431
00:35:07,116 --> 00:35:09,365
I'd probably kill me too.

432
00:35:34,516 --> 00:35:36,480
Looks like they've already been here.

433
00:35:37,796 --> 00:35:41,243
If he was already here, why didn't
he just take out the power himself?

434
00:35:41,677 --> 00:35:43,236
I don't know.

435
00:35:45,275 --> 00:35:46,565
Stop here.

436
00:35:48,836 --> 00:35:50,440
Why?

437
00:35:50,596 --> 00:35:52,483
Ever see what happens to a metal car...

438
00:35:52,635 --> 00:35:55,517
...when it touches a transformer
that powers the whole city?

439
00:35:55,996 --> 00:35:59,041
- Just wait here, I'll handle it.
- What, alone?

440
00:35:59,196 --> 00:36:00,636
Yeah, just be ready to go.

441
00:36:00,996 --> 00:36:02,316
You sure?

442
00:37:00,875 --> 00:37:03,515
Turn the car around,
that's what I should do.

443
00:37:03,675 --> 00:37:05,280
No, I should go in after her.

444
00:37:05,635 --> 00:37:08,003
No, she's fine.
She knows what she's doing.

445
00:37:15,676 --> 00:37:17,804
Hello? I don't have much time.

446
00:37:17,955 --> 00:37:20,475
I'm in this car with this man
and his wife was kidnapped.

447
00:37:20,635 --> 00:37:22,282
<i>I speak English. Calm yourself.</i>

448
00:37:22,436 --> 00:37:24,476
Could you just send someone, please?

449
00:37:24,635 --> 00:37:26,644
<i>- What is your, uh, emergency?
- I don't know.</i>

450
00:37:26,795 --> 00:37:29,599
It's this voice telling us what to do.
You have to help us.

451
00:37:29,756 --> 00:37:32,636
<i>- Exactly what is your location?
- I'm at the power plant.</i>

452
00:37:35,194 --> 00:37:37,082
- You make it so much fun.
- Shit.

453
00:37:37,234 --> 00:37:40,519
Wherever that clever mind takes you,
remember, I've already been there.

454
00:37:40,674 --> 00:37:42,715
<i>Look around.</i>

455
00:37:43,075 --> 00:37:44,558
<i>You see? That's right.</i>

456
00:37:46,475 --> 00:37:49,159
The police will think
you blew up the power station.

457
00:37:52,955 --> 00:37:55,279
Can I give you some advice? Run.

458
00:37:56,795 --> 00:37:58,202
Come on, come on.

459
00:38:03,514 --> 00:38:05,119
- Go, go, go!
- What, what, what?

460
00:38:05,275 --> 00:38:06,879
- Drive, drive! Go!
- What happened?

461
00:38:23,194 --> 00:38:24,559
- Hold on.
- Shit.

462
00:38:33,714 --> 00:38:34,718
Aah!

463
00:38:52,075 --> 00:38:53,199
Faster!

464
00:38:54,554 --> 00:38:56,038
Go faster!

465
00:39:07,554 --> 00:39:08,721
Oh!

466
00:39:47,355 --> 00:39:49,842
What are you doing? What are you doing?

467
00:39:51,034 --> 00:39:52,998
I'm not dying for you.

468
00:39:54,232 --> 00:39:56,678
- What happened?
- This is a part of his plan.

469
00:39:56,834 --> 00:39:59,037
I was on camera that whole time.

470
00:39:59,193 --> 00:40:02,597
He could have easily taken out the power
himself, but he lured us in there because...

471
00:40:02,753 --> 00:40:05,480
...he wanted me
to get caught on camera doing it.

472
00:40:05,633 --> 00:40:08,033
You think the cops
would ever believe me now?

473
00:40:09,073 --> 00:40:12,041
Before, it was just you...

474
00:40:12,192 --> 00:40:13,841
...this car.

